⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Podkayne Fries
node H1 · H1 · ⟦Podkayne Fries:H1:6490ba⟧

WHO   — Podkayne "Poddy" Fries, a bright, charming, Mars-born teenage girl who keeps a diary, dreams of commanding starships, and sets out on her first voyage to Earth chaperoned by her formidable, scheming great-uncle Tom — and her insufferably brilliant little brother Clark.
WHAT  — The diarist-narrator of Podkayne of Mars — a coming-of-age journey from Mars toward Earth that turns out to be a cover for interplanetary politics, and ends with Poddy paying a terrible price for her brother's recklessness and her own warm heart.
WHERE — From Marsopolis on Mars, aboard the liner Tricorn, to Venus and its glittering, dangerous Venusberg.
WHY   — Because she means to be a captain in a universe that keeps telling girls to settle for less — and because she cannot help loving even her devious baby brother, a tenderness that becomes both her glory and her undoing.
HOW   — By wit, observation, and an irrepressible diary voice — charming everyone aboard while the adults play a deadlier game around her, and finally by an act of selfless courage toward a stranded creature.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  A girl from Mars can aim at the stars — and a soft heart is courage, not weakness.

